<i>Just fight it out</i>

48
00:02:48,233 --> 00:02:50,192
<i>Just fight it out</i>

49
00:02:51,317 --> 00:02:53,275
<i>Just fight it out</i>

50
00:04:15,775 --> 00:04:17,400
[FILO]
Mel, uhm...

51
00:04:17,483 --> 00:04:19,442
[rustling]

52
00:04:19,525 --> 00:04:21,525
[RAPHTALIA]
Master Naofumi.

53
00:04:21,608 --> 00:04:23,275
[NAOFUMI]
How'd it go?

54
00:04:23,358 --> 00:04:24,775
The altered images
have made their way

55
00:04:24,858 --> 00:04:27,817
to almost all the nearby
towns and villages.

56
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:30,317
Entering them
would be too risky.

57
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,817
I see...

58
00:04:32,858 --> 00:04:34,608
[RAPHTALIA]
Wait, isn't that...

59
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:37,983
What was the point
of trying to kill

60
00:04:38,067 --> 00:04:40,650
the second princess
right in front of us?

61
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:41,983
[KNIGHT 13A]
Hmph.

62
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,025
Y'hear what I said?!

63
00:04:45,108 --> 00:04:46,400
I have nothing
to say to the devil,

64
00:04:46,483 --> 00:04:48,358
so you can kill me now!

65
00:04:53,525 --> 00:04:55,650
That's a rosary from
the Three Heroes Church.

66
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:57,275
Wait, the Three Heroes Church?

67
00:04:57,358 --> 00:04:59,858
They worship the Sword,
Spear, and Bow Heroes.

68
00:04:59,942 --> 00:05:01,817
It's Melromarc's state religion.

69
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,108
That's weird, I saw one of these

70
00:05:03,192 --> 00:05:05,150
at the church
in the capital, too.

71
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:08,192
Yeah, all the heroes
except the shield, huh?

72
00:05:08,275 --> 00:05:09,317
[KNIGHT 13A]
You will pay the price

73
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,150
of disturbing
the natural order!

74
00:05:11,233 --> 00:05:13,067
And you'll suffer for it!!

75
00:05:14,817 --> 00:05:16,983
[RAPHTALIA]
What was he talking about?

76
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:18,525
Y'got me, Raphtalia.

77
00:05:18,608 --> 00:05:20,608
One of the king's
harebrained ideas.

78
00:05:20,692 --> 00:05:22,733
And thanks to the
stupidity of her father,

79
00:05:22,817 --> 00:05:25,983
we're stuck here
with nowhere to go.

80
00:05:26,067 --> 00:05:28,317
[MELTY]
My father can't be behind this.

81
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,358
Yeah, right, and who else

82
00:05:29,442 --> 00:05:31,233
could've ordered
something like that?

83
00:05:32,275 --> 00:05:34,233
My sister, probably.

84
00:05:34,317 --> 00:05:36,650
So she's trying to kill
you and take your place

85
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:38,858
as crown princess,
is that what you're saying?

86
00:05:38,942 --> 00:05:40,442
[MELTY]
Mm.

87
00:05:40,525 --> 00:05:41,983
[NAOFUMI]
But I know that those knights

88
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:45,483
who attacked us are under
the king's direct control.

89
00:05:45,567 --> 00:05:49,150
It'd be natural to assume he's
in the middle of everything.

90
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:51,817
If I'm right, those guys--

91
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:53,692
there's nothing they'd
love more than to frame

92
00:05:53,775 --> 00:05:56,858
the mythical "Devil of the
Shield" for this whole thing.

93
00:05:56,942 --> 00:05:59,483
[MELTY] Father would never
stoop to something so low!

94
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:02,275
What makes you so sure, kid?

95
00:06:02,358 --> 00:06:05,858
[MELTY]
Because... Because Father is...

96
00:06:05,942 --> 00:06:08,192
I don't know how you
can stick up for him.

97
00:06:08,275 --> 00:06:10,025
That scumbag...

98
00:06:10,983 --> 00:06:12,400
But you're wrong.

99
00:06:12,483 --> 00:06:13,942
How so?

100
00:06:14,025 --> 00:06:15,817
You're totally wrong!

101
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:18,025
Why can't either
of you understand?

102
00:06:18,108 --> 00:06:19,775
We don't have time
to fight each other,

103
00:06:19,858 --> 00:06:22,983
there are problems before us
we need to solve together!

104
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,150
Please!

105
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:26,733
Talk to Father one
more time, I beg you!

106
00:06:27,650 --> 00:06:29,483
[RAPHTALIA]
Master Naofumi...

107
00:06:31,317 --> 00:06:32,608
I can't...

108
00:06:32,692 --> 00:06:35,067
How will I ever
face Mother like this?!

109
00:06:35,150 --> 00:06:37,150
I just can't do it!

110
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:39,275
You don't have to cry, Mel.

111
00:06:39,358 --> 00:06:41,067
I'm still here for you.

112
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:47,108
[MELTY sobbing]

113
00:06:53,358 --> 00:06:54,900
We're out of time.

114
00:06:57,192 --> 00:06:58,983
[FILO]
Master.

115
00:06:59,067 --> 00:07:00,483
Welcome back.

116
00:07:00,567 --> 00:07:01,650
[MELTY]
Hmph!

117
00:07:03,358 --> 00:07:04,983
[NAOFUMI]
Listen.

118
00:07:05,067 --> 00:07:07,733
We're going to have
to leave the country.

119
00:07:07,817 --> 00:07:09,817
So what'll you do?

120
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,858
I'll return to the
capital somehow.

121
00:07:11,942 --> 00:07:13,150
I have to talk to Father and--

122
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:14,650
--[NAOFUMI] Lousy idea.
--[gasps]

123
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:17,733
[NAOFUMI] You go back now,
you'd only get yourself killed.

124
00:07:17,817 --> 00:07:20,275
However, if you were to change
your mind and stay with us,

125
00:07:20,358 --> 00:07:22,900
I'll keep you safe.

126
00:07:22,983 --> 00:07:25,692
I can promise you that,
if nothing else.

127
00:07:27,108 --> 00:07:29,483
Oh, come with us, please.

128
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:31,192
All right.

129
00:07:31,275 --> 00:07:32,983
[NAOFUMI]
We'll leave before dawn.

130
00:07:33,067 --> 00:07:34,650
Make sure you're ready.

131
00:07:34,733 --> 00:07:35,900
Master Naofumi,

132
00:07:35,983 --> 00:07:38,858
where are we going to
be traveling this time?

133
00:07:38,942 --> 00:07:41,108
Don't worry,
I'll let you know...

134
00:07:55,192 --> 00:07:57,275
What about the wagon?

135
00:07:57,358 --> 00:07:59,025
Come on, you knew the deal.

136
00:07:59,108 --> 00:08:01,900
There's no way we could
cross this range on a wagon.

137
00:08:01,983 --> 00:08:04,942
We'll come back for it
once this thing's over.

138
00:08:05,025 --> 00:08:06,108
[FILO]
Promise?

139
00:08:06,192 --> 00:08:07,942
You promise
we'll come back for it?

140
00:08:08,025 --> 00:08:09,525
[NAOFUMI]
I promise.

141
00:08:42,900 --> 00:08:45,108
Let's take
a little break in here.

142
00:08:45,192 --> 00:08:46,525
Okay!

143
00:08:47,983 --> 00:08:49,567
[NAOFUMI]
You all right, Princess?

144
00:08:49,650 --> 00:08:51,358
Fine, thank you.

145
00:08:52,983 --> 00:08:55,942
She must be
tired after everything.

146
00:08:56,025 --> 00:08:58,317
Master Naofumi,
why did you choose

147
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,733
the kingdom of Siltvelt over
all the other possibilities?

148
00:09:01,817 --> 00:09:03,692
The extra security.

149
00:09:03,775 --> 00:09:06,442
There's gotta be a really good
reason they're trying so hard

150
00:09:06,525 --> 00:09:08,983
to prevent us
from getting there.

151
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:11,567
It might just be the
perfect place to hide out.

152
00:09:11,650 --> 00:09:13,942
Ah! Right!

153
00:09:24,775 --> 00:09:26,233
[MELTY]
Father...

154
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:30,817
There's something I need
to ask you, Sir Shield Hero.

155
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:33,150
What happened
between you and Father?

156
00:09:37,317 --> 00:09:39,692
[MELTY]
I mean, my mother said

157
00:09:39,775 --> 00:09:42,650
that the Shield Hero
should be treated well.

158
00:09:42,733 --> 00:09:44,733
What happened?

159
00:09:44,817 --> 00:09:46,858
Come to think of it,
now that you mention it,

160
00:09:46,942 --> 00:09:49,233
I don't know a single
thing about your mom.

161
00:09:49,317 --> 00:09:50,483
What's to say?

162
00:09:50,567 --> 00:09:52,442
She's the queen of
the country of Melromarc.

163
00:09:52,525 --> 00:09:53,525
Queen, huh?

164
00:09:53,608 --> 00:09:55,525
Yes, that means
she's higher than Father

165
00:09:55,608 --> 00:09:56,983
in the pecking order.

166
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:59,108
Wait, how come the queen's
more powerful than the king?

167
00:09:59,192 --> 00:10:02,733
Melromarc is a country
based on matrilineal succession.

168
00:10:02,817 --> 00:10:04,233
Gimme a break!

169
00:10:04,317 --> 00:10:07,317
You mean the king married
into the royal family?

170
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,900
What's so funny about that?

171
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:11,733
Nothing except for the fact that
he acts like he runs the joint.

172
00:10:11,817 --> 00:10:13,233
[MELTY]
Well, he is the king, after all!

173
00:10:13,317 --> 00:10:14,983
So he's like adopted royalty?

174
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:16,400
[RAPHTALIA gasps]

175
00:10:17,983 --> 00:10:19,317
[NAOFUMI]
Time to go.

176
00:10:36,775 --> 00:10:38,733
[KNIGHT 13G]
They're not over here.

177
00:10:38,817 --> 00:10:40,233
[KNIGHT 13H]
They can't have gone far.

178
00:10:40,317 --> 00:10:41,567
Find them!

179
00:10:54,692 --> 00:11:00,150
[KNIGHTS chattering]

180
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:02,483
They've blocked
this route off, too.

181
00:11:02,567 --> 00:11:04,525
We'll have to find another path.

182
00:11:08,192 --> 00:11:09,817
[MELTY screams]

183
00:11:16,525 --> 00:11:18,900
[KNIGHT 13I]
There they are! Down there!

184
00:11:18,983 --> 00:11:20,817
Looks like we're
gonna have company.

185
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:22,233
Can you run?

186
00:11:22,317 --> 00:11:24,025
I think.

187
00:11:24,108 --> 00:11:26,817
[NAOFUMI] We'll make a break
for it past that big rock!

188
00:11:26,900 --> 00:11:31,358
[KNIGHTS shouting]

189
00:11:44,067 --> 00:11:46,525
That's it, you've got
nowhere left to run.

190
00:11:46,608 --> 00:11:47,650
You're surrounded.

191
00:11:47,733 --> 00:11:49,858
Even you have to admit that.

192
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:53,692
Cease your resistance and
release Princess Melty at once.

193
00:11:53,775 --> 00:11:55,233
What's with this
"release" business?

194
00:11:55,317 --> 00:11:57,150
It's not like I have
her tied up or anything.

195
00:11:57,233 --> 00:11:58,650
Quit lying to us.

196
00:11:58,733 --> 00:12:00,525
We have all the
proof we need now.

197
00:12:00,608 --> 00:12:01,983
Please, Sir Heroes.

198
00:12:02,067 --> 00:12:04,442
I'm perfectly fine,
as you can well see.

199
00:12:04,525 --> 00:12:08,108
The Shield Hero kept watch
over me, making sure I was safe.

200
00:12:08,192 --> 00:12:09,692
Wait a minute.

201
00:12:09,775 --> 00:12:13,150
This whole thing is happening
because Naofumi abducted you.

202
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:14,858
This is all a misunderstanding.

203
00:12:14,942 --> 00:12:17,358
You see, someone is
plotting to have me killed.

204
00:12:17,442 --> 00:12:21,567
I asked him to take me with
him and to protect my life.

205
00:12:21,650 --> 00:12:23,692
He's protecting you? Come on!

206
00:12:23,775 --> 00:12:26,358
[MELTY] What advantage could
the Shield Hero possibly stand

207
00:12:26,442 --> 00:12:28,900
to gain by abducting me?

208
00:12:28,983 --> 00:12:30,567
The queen told me

209
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:33,608
this is the time for all
of us to work together.

210
00:12:33,692 --> 00:12:38,067
It's the only way we'll be able
to thwart the catastrophes.

211
00:12:38,150 --> 00:12:39,775
Our world can't
withstand any more

212
00:12:39,858 --> 00:12:43,358
of these ridiculous,
pointless conflicts!

213
00:12:43,442 --> 00:12:46,233
Put your weapons away, please!

214
00:12:46,317 --> 00:12:49,650
Like she says, this whole thing
was a setup from the beginning.

215
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:50,817
I have no secrets.

216
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:53,192
I'll tell you everything
I know. And then--

217
00:12:53,275 --> 00:12:56,192
[MYNE] I command you
not to listen to him!

218
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:59,400
That lying devil possesses
a brainwashing shield!

219
00:12:59,483 --> 00:13:02,817
It allows him take over your
mind by simply talking to you--

220
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:05,483
it's the most dangerous
weapon he has!

221
00:13:05,567 --> 00:13:06,858
Wha...?

222
00:13:06,942 --> 00:13:08,733
Who would believe something
so stupid and silly?!

223
00:13:08,817 --> 00:13:11,525
The Three Heroes Church
has discovered that heretics

224
00:13:11,608 --> 00:13:14,483
who worship the Shield have
started popping up all over

225
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:16,775
the kingdom in the past month.

226
00:13:16,858 --> 00:13:18,942
The Three Heroes Church again?

227
00:13:19,025 --> 00:13:20,817
The Devil of the Shield
calls himself

228
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,775
"the Savior of
the Heavenly Fowl"

229
00:13:22,858 --> 00:13:25,108
and goes around
brainwashing the innocent!

230
00:13:25,192 --> 00:13:26,817
Sister, you're mad!

231
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:29,942
Melty, my dear, little,
deranged creature!

232
00:13:30,025 --> 00:13:31,775
It's obvious that
Devil of the Shield

233
00:13:31,858 --> 00:13:34,025
has already brainwashed you.

234
00:13:34,108 --> 00:13:35,442
Now I see!

235
00:13:35,525 --> 00:13:36,900
That means that
Raphtalia and Filo

236
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:39,067
were brainwashed
by Naofumi, too.

237
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:40,317
No, you're wrong!

238
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,692
Master Naofumi hasn't
brainwashed any of us!

239
00:13:42,775 --> 00:13:44,942
If my shield really
had the ability to do that,

240
00:13:45,025 --> 00:13:48,067
we wouldn't be in this damned
situation in the first place!

241
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:50,442
Do we have a
guarantee that it can't?

242
00:13:50,525 --> 00:13:52,233
What kind of proof can
you give to convince us

243
00:13:52,317 --> 00:13:54,150
that you're not lying?

244
00:13:55,358 --> 00:13:58,025
Naofumi, hand over
the princess right now,

245
00:13:58,108 --> 00:14:00,067
and no one'll get hurt.

246
00:14:00,150 --> 00:14:03,025
I promise you she won't
be harmed in any way.

247
00:14:03,108 --> 00:14:05,525
[gasps]

248
00:14:05,608 --> 00:14:09,858
You know, if we can
avoid all this fighting,

249
00:14:09,942 --> 00:14:12,233
I guess it might
be for the best.

250
00:14:13,608 --> 00:14:16,483
[MYNE] You are
absolutely right, Sir Ren!

251
00:14:16,567 --> 00:14:20,692
I'm so glad we all agree that
Melty's safety comes first!

252
00:14:23,025 --> 00:14:24,608
[gasps]

253
00:14:26,525 --> 00:14:28,317
Come.

254
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:31,317
Let's all go home together now.

255
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,900
No...

256
00:14:32,983 --> 00:14:35,483
If I go, I'll be killed!

257
00:14:42,567 --> 00:14:45,650
[MYNE] Come to me,
dearest little sister.

258
00:14:46,942 --> 00:14:48,942
Please, Sir Hero!

259
00:14:49,025 --> 00:14:50,608
Please help!

260
00:14:56,900 --> 00:15:00,400
Y'know, Ren, I have to admit
that your offer is generous,

261
00:15:00,483 --> 00:15:03,858
but I just do not trust that
woman with the princess.

262
00:15:04,817 --> 00:15:07,025
What are you suggesting?

263
00:15:07,108 --> 00:15:08,692
[RAPHTALIA gasps]

264
00:15:08,775 --> 00:15:09,775
[inaudible]

265
00:15:09,858 --> 00:15:11,608
What's that devil
talking about now?

266
00:15:11,692 --> 00:15:13,483
Melty is my
dearest little sister,

267
00:15:13,567 --> 00:15:15,025
I wouldn't dream of anything--

268
00:15:15,108 --> 00:15:17,650
Come off it, lady,
you're not fooling anyone.

269
00:15:17,733 --> 00:15:19,400
You want to be crown
princess so badly

270
00:15:19,483 --> 00:15:21,317
you'd kill your own sister!

271
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,317
You'll say you're undoing
the "brainwashing"

272
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:25,775
and then kill her
when nobody's looking.

273
00:15:25,858 --> 00:15:28,650
I'll bet that's exactly
what you're planning!

274
00:15:30,192 --> 00:15:32,983
Don't forget, I promised
to keep you safe.

275
00:15:34,025 --> 00:15:34,983
Filo, now!

276
00:15:35,067 --> 00:15:36,775
'Kay!

277
00:15:42,025 --> 00:15:43,483
Ready when you are!

278
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:44,733
[MYNE yelps]

279
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:48,108
Air Strike Shield now!

280
00:15:59,442 --> 00:16:01,608
Not so fast!

281
00:16:04,025 --> 00:16:07,442
[ALL screaming]

282
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:20,067
[NAOFUMI gasps]

283
00:16:29,858 --> 00:16:31,192
[NAOFUMI gasps]

284
00:16:33,442 --> 00:16:34,567
I've called for backup,

285
00:16:34,650 --> 00:16:37,400
so it's too late for
you to try to escape.

286
00:16:39,983 --> 00:16:42,400
I can't get this off.
It's... Huh?

287
00:16:42,483 --> 00:16:44,858
--[shrieks]
--You're finally mine, Filo!

288
00:16:44,942 --> 00:16:46,567
Let go of me, help!

289
00:16:46,650 --> 00:16:48,317
I've lost all my strength!

290
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,442
--Please let go of me!
--I had the royal alchemists

291
00:16:50,525 --> 00:16:52,025
come up with this
ankle bracelet for ya.

292
00:16:52,108 --> 00:16:55,317
So now you're gonna stay my
little angel forever and ever!

293
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,650
[MELTY] As source of
thy power, I order thee.

294
00:16:57,733 --> 00:17:00,400
Decipher the laws of
nature and slice through

295
00:17:00,483 --> 00:17:02,858
my target like a blade of water.

296
00:17:02,942 --> 00:17:05,400
Zweit Aqua Slash!

297
00:17:08,483 --> 00:17:09,525
Let her go!

298
00:17:09,608 --> 00:17:11,858
I'm not gonna miss next time!

299
00:17:17,942 --> 00:17:19,442
Myne, wait a sec!

300
00:17:19,525 --> 00:17:21,650
Are you trying to kill
your sister Melty?!

301
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:24,442
I have to defend myself
since she attacked first!

302
00:17:24,525 --> 00:17:25,942
Zweit Hellfire!

303
00:17:26,025 --> 00:17:28,025
Zweit Fire Arrow!

304
00:17:29,608 --> 00:17:30,650
What are you doing?!

305
00:17:30,733 --> 00:17:32,192
Stop now!

306
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:37,442
To save her from Naofumi's
brainwashing, she must die!

307
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:42,358
Master Naofumi...

308
00:17:42,442 --> 00:17:45,025
Can I leave Mel with you
for a bit? I'll be right back.

309
00:17:45,108 --> 00:17:47,025
[NAOFUMI]
Sure.

310
00:17:47,108 --> 00:17:48,817
Step back a little.

311
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:51,067
All right...

312
00:17:51,150 --> 00:17:53,900
Come forth, Rage Shield!

313
00:17:53,983 --> 00:17:57,525
Here I come, Filo... [giggles]

314
00:17:57,608 --> 00:17:58,858
Huh?

315
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,900
[NAOFUMI yelling]

316
00:18:02,983 --> 00:18:04,608
What's with the shield?

317
00:18:06,733 --> 00:18:11,358
Bring down the hammer of justice
on the Devil of the Shield!

318
00:18:11,442 --> 00:18:13,358
Archers, fire!

319
00:18:18,317 --> 00:18:19,525
[gasps]

320
00:18:25,275 --> 00:18:27,275
Not on my watch.

321
00:18:32,233 --> 00:18:34,192
It's my turn now!

322
00:18:34,275 --> 00:18:36,733
[yells]

323
00:18:37,983 --> 00:18:41,442
Annihilate the Devil of the
Shield and his whole party!

324
00:18:41,525 --> 00:18:43,858
[KNIGHTS yelling]

325
00:18:43,942 --> 00:18:45,733
[REN]
Wait, don't!

326
00:18:48,192 --> 00:18:50,567
[KNIGHTS yelling]

327
00:18:53,483 --> 00:18:54,733
[KNIGHTS scream]

328
00:18:54,817 --> 00:18:56,817
That light, what is it?

329
00:19:06,067 --> 00:19:08,358
[REN]
What the hell's going on?

330
00:19:08,442 --> 00:19:10,275
[NAOFUMI]
Ren...

331
00:19:10,358 --> 00:19:13,108
I know you'll be able
to figure this all out--

332
00:19:13,192 --> 00:19:16,025
what's really happening here.

333
00:19:16,108 --> 00:19:17,900
Wait, Naofumi!

334
00:19:34,650 --> 00:19:36,233
[FILO]
Yay!

335
00:19:37,942 --> 00:19:39,108
[rustling]

336
00:19:41,817 --> 00:19:43,108
[MELTY]
Wait!

337
00:19:43,192 --> 00:19:45,608
She's on our side.

338
00:19:45,692 --> 00:19:47,025
That's one of the Shadows,

339
00:19:47,108 --> 00:19:50,525
an espionage squad under
the queen's direct control.

340
00:19:50,608 --> 00:19:52,233
Sir Shield Hero,

341
00:19:52,317 --> 00:19:53,775
this is the first time
I'm meeting you

342
00:19:53,858 --> 00:19:55,692
in this form, I daresay.

343
00:19:55,775 --> 00:19:58,108
"Daresay." What's that about?

344
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:02,775
[SHADOW] Allow me to
get straight to the point.

345
00:20:02,858 --> 00:20:06,317
Sir Shield Hero, you are
hereby requested to meet with

346
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:08,233
Her Majesty the Queen.

347
00:20:08,317 --> 00:20:09,817
With the queen?

348
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:12,817
The roots of this commotion
go deep, you understand?

349
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:16,108
I daresay we would appreciate
all the help you can give.

350
00:20:16,192 --> 00:20:18,858
This abduction and the events
leading up to it were set up

351
00:20:18,942 --> 00:20:22,108
by those who find your
accomplishments alarming.

352
00:20:22,192 --> 00:20:23,233
Oh, that's terrific,

353
00:20:23,317 --> 00:20:25,358
more pains in the
butt to deal handle.

354
00:20:25,442 --> 00:20:27,150
Yeah? So?

355
00:20:27,233 --> 00:20:28,775
What would I gain
by meeting with her?

356
00:20:28,858 --> 00:20:30,775
I have no doubt you'll
understand better

357
00:20:30,858 --> 00:20:33,233
after you've met, I daresay.

358
00:20:39,108 --> 00:20:40,900
[NAOFUMI] The queen's
in the opposite direction

359
00:20:40,983 --> 00:20:42,692
from Siltvelt.

360
00:20:43,650 --> 00:20:47,233
Hey, Second Princess, you know
anything about this country?

361
00:20:48,525 --> 00:20:50,525
Oh, yeah, Second Princess.

362
00:20:50,608 --> 00:20:53,233
You know how to
use magic, don't you?

363
00:20:53,317 --> 00:20:55,608
[MELTY]
Don't call me that.

364
00:20:55,692 --> 00:20:56,983
[NAOFUMI]
What was that, Second Princess?

365
00:20:57,067 --> 00:20:59,067
Stop calling me Second Princess!

366
00:20:59,150 --> 00:21:01,650
What's gotten into
you all of a sudden?

367
00:21:04,358 --> 00:21:07,150
I have a name,
and it's Melty, that's what!

368
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:08,942
Why on earth do
you keep calling me

369
00:21:09,025 --> 00:21:11,275
"Second Princess," Shield Hero?

370
00:21:11,358 --> 00:21:14,483
You keep treating me like
I'm just an outsider!

371
00:21:14,567 --> 00:21:15,733
Hey, you're the only
one around here

372
00:21:15,817 --> 00:21:17,900
calling me "Shield
Hero," y'know.

373
00:21:17,983 --> 00:21:20,317
Well then... I'll have
to call you Naofumi.

374
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:23,983
And you can call me Melty,
which is what I prefer anyway.

375
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:26,608
So tell me, Naofumi,
what's it going to be?

376
00:21:26,692 --> 00:21:28,567
Straight to his first name?

377
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:30,983
Well, Second Princess,
y'see, it's like this...

378
00:21:31,067 --> 00:21:32,733
--Hey, wait!
--[NAOFUMI] Okay.

379
00:21:32,817 --> 00:21:34,108
[NAOFUMI]
Melty.

380
00:21:34,192 --> 00:21:35,483
Happy now?

381
00:21:35,567 --> 00:21:37,108
Once again, please...

382
00:21:37,192 --> 00:21:38,567
Huh?

383
00:21:38,650 --> 00:21:41,067
[MELTY]
Say my name one more time.

384
00:21:41,150 --> 00:21:42,400
Fine, Melty.

385
00:21:42,483 --> 00:21:45,775
Good. And I suggest
you don't forget it, either.

386
00:21:45,858 --> 00:21:47,400
One more thing...

387
00:21:47,483 --> 00:21:49,483
Thanks for that.

388
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:51,942
[NAOFUMI]
Hmm? What's up?

389
00:21:52,025 --> 00:21:53,025
Nothing!

390
00:21:53,108 --> 00:21:54,483
I'm fine, just forget it.

391
00:21:54,567 --> 00:21:55,817
[gasps]

392
00:21:57,942 --> 00:22:00,317
Where's that smell coming from?

393
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:16,858
[MYNE giggling]

